{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Update your code to make use of the new state sharing tools in the library, such as the "},{"code":"Shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"property wrapper, and the "},{"code":"appStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"fileStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" persistence strategies."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.16","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.15","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.14","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.13","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.12","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.11","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.9","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.8","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.7","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.6","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.5","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.4"],"generated":true}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.10"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"title":"Migrating to 1.10","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. This version of the library only introduced new"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"APIs and did not deprecate any existing APIs."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Before following this migration guide be sure you have fully migrated to the newest","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tools of version 1.9. See "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"},{"text":" for more information.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Important","style":"important","type":"aside"},{"level":2,"text":"Sharing state","type":"heading","anchor":"Sharing-state"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The new tools added are concerned with allowing one to seamlessly share state with many parts of an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"application that is easy to understand, and most importantly, testable. See the dedicated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" article for more information on how to use these new tools."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To share state in one feature with another feature, simply use the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Shared"},{"type":"text","text":" property wrapper:"}]},{"code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared var signUpData: SignUpData","  \/\/ ...","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This will require that "},{"code":"SignUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" be passed in from the parent, and any changes made to this state"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"will be instantly observed by all features holding onto it.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Further, there are persistence strategies one can employ in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Shared"},{"text":". For example, if you want any","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"changes of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signUpData"},{"text":" to be automatically persisted to the file system you can use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"fileStorage(_:decoder:encoder:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and specify a URL:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared(.fileStorage(URL(\/* ... *\/) var signUpData = SignUpData()","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Upon app launch the ","type":"text"},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be populated from disk, and any changes made to "},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will automatically be persisted to disk. Further, if the disk version changes, all instances of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signUpData"},{"type":"text","text":" in the application will automatically update."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"There is another persistence strategy for storing simple data types in user defaults, called","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"appStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". It can refer to a value in user defaults by a string","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"key:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@ObservableState ","struct State {","  @Shared(.appStorage(\"isOn\")) var isOn = false","  \/\/ ...","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Similar to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileStorage(_:decoder:encoder:)"},{"type":"text","text":", upon launch of the application the initial"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"value of "},{"code":"isOn","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be populated from user defaults, and any change to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isOn"},{"type":"text","text":" will be automatically"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"persisted to user defaults. Further, if the user defaults value changes, all instances of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isOn"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in the application will automatically update."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That is the basics of sharing data. Be sure to see the dedicated "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState"},{"text":" article","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for more detailed information.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.10"},"references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture/MigratingTo1.4":{"url":"\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.4","abstract":[{"text":"Update your code to make use of the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer()"},{"text":" macro, and learn how to b